org.apps8os.trafficsense

Class TrafficsenseContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apps8os.trafficsense.TrafficsenseContainer

  • public class TrafficsenseContainer
extends java.lang.Object
    Singleton for TrafficSense journey tracker. Application using TrafficSense must first obtain an instance of this object by invoking getInstance(). All entities such as Activity and Service interacting with the singleton must invoke activityAttach(Context) or serviceAttach(Context) before other operations. The entity must invoke activityDetach() or serviceDetach() after it finishes its work with the singleton.

      • activityAttach

        public void activityAttach(Context ctx)
        Attach an Activity to the singleton. Should generally be invoked from an Activity before any other operations. If the singleton is uninitialized, it is initialized and the Context supplied is used for all further operations. Otherwise, the Context is ignored.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the Context to be associated.

      • activityDetach

        public void activityDetach()
        Detach an Activity from the singleton. Should be invoked in onPause(). Release resources if there is no one else attached.

      • serviceAttach

        public boolean serviceAttach(Context ctx)
        Attach a Service and a Context to the singleton. A Service should attach to the singleton before any other operations. The singleton cannot be initialized by a Service since services can be restarted automatically by Android. A Service receiving false from this method should not perform any further operations with the singleton.
        Parameters:
        ctx - (currently unused).
        Returns:
        true if successfully attached.

      • serviceDetach

        public void serviceDetach()
        Detach the Service from the singleton. Should be invoked in onDestroy(). Release resources if there is no one else attached.

      • isJourneyStarted

        Whether at least one journey tracker service is active.
        Returns:
        true if at least one journey tracker service is active.

      • stopJourney

        public void stopJourney()
        Stop following current journey. Stops all running tracker services. Does not reset current progress in mRoute.

      • startJourneyTracker

        public void startJourneyTracker(int serviceType,
                       EmailCredential credential)
        Retrieve and start following a journey in a separate Thread. Retrieves a journey from an e-mail account. GPS coordinates are retrieved if the desired service is location-based. Then starts the specified tracker service for the journey. This is expected to be invoked from an Activity. Starts a new Thread in order to keep working in case the calling Activity becomes invisible before the service is started.
        Parameters:
        serviceType - type of journey tracker service desired.
        credential - account details for accessing mailbox.
        See Also:
        for supported serviceTypes.

      • startTrackerService

        public void startTrackerService(int serviceType)
        Launch the journey tracker service selected. Route must have been set before invoking this method. (such as via parseJourney() or setRoute(Route). Types currently supported are: SERVICE_TIME_ONLY and SERVICE_LOCATION_ONLY. Pebble UI is initialized here.
        Parameters:
        serviceType - type of journey tracker service to launch.
        See Also:
        Constants

        Retrieve the journey text from the last message in the inbox of the given account. This method perform possibly long network operations. Must NOT invoke this from the main/UI thread.

      • retrieveJourney

        public void retrieveJourney(EmailCredential credential,
                   View update,
                   java.lang.Runnable after)
        Retrieves a journey in plain text from the given e-mail account. The result is stored in mJourneyText. May optionally update an UI element after completion. Currently it is the last mail in inbox.
        Parameters:
        credential - e-mail account to be accessed.
        update - UI element to be updated. (optional)
